SESSION TIMEOUT
PROMPT FOR REPLIT AGENT

Remove all automatic logout behaviour from the app.
I want the authentication system to behave like ChatGPT, where the user stays logged in all day unless they manually choose to log out.
Do the following:

Disable any “session timeout” or “force logout after inactivity” logic in the backend and frontend.

Ensure the authentication cookie or token uses a long expiry time, such as 7–30 days.

If using Streamlit’s st.session_state, ensure it persists across reruns.

If using JWT or API tokens, extend their expiration.

Check the codebase for any logout triggers (functions, timers, callbacks) and remove them.

Keep the explicit manual logout button, but do not trigger logout automatically for any reason.

Do NOT clear session_state unless the user clicks logout.

Expected result:
The user logs in once and stays logged in indefinitely, with no auto-logouts, even across reruns or when the tab is left open all day.